s.com/markets/deals/amazons-irobot-deal-eu-antitrust-crosshairs-2023-07-06/"><em>路透社</em></a>，该公司将“继续与欧盟委员会合作完成整个流程，并专注于解决现阶段的问题和任何已确定的担忧。”他们还告诉新闻机构，亚马逊可以“为 iRobot 这样的公司提供资源，以加速创新并投资于关键功能，同时降低消费者的价格。”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/amazons-irobot-purchase-is-under-investigation-by-european-authorities-054857108.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/amazons-irobot-purchase-is-under-investigation-by-european-authorities-054857108.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 3e25d3ab-6b9a-438d-9917-9e960085994f</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jul 2023 05:48:57 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688708940</ingested><modified> 2023-07-07T05:49:05+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Personal Investing Ideas & Strategies]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="4480" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-images/2019-12/7c760980-2b2b-11ea-9fb7-b1ca51cfa979" width="6720"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4480" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-images/2019-12/7c760980-2b2b-11ea-9fb7-b1ca51cfa979" width="6720"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Onfokus via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Laval, Сanada - December 10, 2016:  iRobot Roomba 980 Cleaning Vacuum on a ceramic floor. iRobot Corp. is a US Company that makes the Roomba and Scooba floor-cleaning machines.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[iRobot Roomba 980 Cleaning Vacuum]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[French Assembly passes bill allowing police to remotely activate phone cameras and microphones for surveillance]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>法国执法部门可能很快就会拥有广泛的权力来窥探涉嫌犯罪的人。法国国民议会议员<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.lemonde.fr/en/france/article/2023/07/06/france-set-to-allow-police-to-spy-through-phones_6044269_7.html">通过了</a>一项法案，允许警方通过远程激活手机和其他设备上的摄像头、麦克风和 GPS 定位系统来监视嫌疑人。据<em>《世界报》</em>报道，法官必须批准使用这些权力，最近修订的法案禁止对记者、律师和其他“敏感职业”使用这些权力。该措施还旨在限制对严重病例的使用，且最多只能使用六个月。地理定位仅限于可判处至少五年监禁的犯罪行为。</p><p>该法案的早期版本已在参议院获得通过，但修正案需要立法机构的批准才能成为法律。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>公民自由倡导者感到震惊。数字版权组织 La Quadrature du Net 此前<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.laquadrature.net/2023/05/31/transformer-les-objets-connectes-en-mouchards-la-surenchere-securitaire-du-gouvernement/">指出</a>了滥用的可能性。由于该法案没有明确什么构成严重犯罪，人们担心法国政府可能会利用该法案来针对环保活动人士和其他不构成严重威胁的人。该组织还指出，令人担忧的安全政策往往会扩大到不太严重的犯罪行为。 La Quadrature 表示，基因登记最初仅用于性犯罪者，但现在已用于大多数犯罪。</p><p>该组织进一步指出，远程访问可能取决于安全漏洞。 La Quadrature 表示，警方将利用安全漏洞，而不是告诉制造商如何修补这些漏洞。</p><p>司法部长埃里克·杜邦-莫雷蒂表示，这些权力每年只会用于“数十起”案件，这与奥威尔<em>1984 年</em>的监视状态“相去甚远”。这位政客认为，这将拯救生命。</p><p>这项立法出台之际，人们对政府设备监控的担忧日益加剧。 NSO 集团遭到强烈反对，据称该集团的 Pegasus 间谍软件被滥用来监视持不同政见者、活动人士<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/pegasus-spyware-found-on-phones-of-mexican-presidents-close-ally-154511274.html">甚至政客</a>。虽然法国的法案更有针对性，但它并不能完全让那些担心政府越权的人放心。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/french-assemble-passes-bill-allowing-police-to-remotely-activate-phone-cameras-and-microphones-for-surveillance-210539401.html ?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/french-assembly-passes-bill-allowing-police-to-remotely-activate-phone-cameras-and-microphones-for-surveillance-210539401.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> e7bba862-dc1f-4310-b921-fc2b6fcbd660</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 06 Jul 2023 21:07:03 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688677623</ingested><modified> 2023-07-06T21:07:10+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Company Legal & Law Matters]]></category><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Society & Culture]]></category><category><![CDATA[Crime & Justice]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="3954" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/1c610250-1c38-11ee-be7f-5c0a11d25a2e" width="5930"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3954" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/1c610250-1c38-11ee-be7f-5c0a11d25a2e" width="5930"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Gonzalo Fuentes / reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A man takes a picture with his mobile phone as French gendarmes block the access to the Constitutional Council (Conseil Constitutionnel) the day of its decision on the admissibility of the government's pension reform law, which was adopted in parliament without a vote, using the 49.3 clause of the constitution, in Paris, France, April 14, 2023.   REUTERS/Gonzalo Fuentes]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[FRANCE-PENSIONS/CONSTITUTION]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best Chromebooks you can buy in 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>鉴于当今市场上的型号繁多，根据您的需求和预算选择最好的 Chromebook 可能很困难。多年的软件更新和笔记本电脑制造商制造出功能更强大、性能更好的笔记本电脑相结合，意味着有大量优秀的 Chrome 操作系统机器可以作为日常驱动程序正常工作。但在选择 Chromebook 之前，您应该牢记一些特殊因素。从 Lenovo IdeaPad Flex 5i 到 Acer Chromebook Spin 714，我们的首选将帮助您确定哪款 Chromebook 值得您购买。</p><h2>什么是 Chrome 操作系统？为什么我要在 Windows 上使用它？</h2><p>这可能是有关 Chromebook 的第一个问题。市场上有很多廉价的 Windows 笔记本电脑，那么为什么还要费心使用 Chrome 操作系统呢？很高兴你问了。对我来说，Chrome 操作系统的简单和干净的本质是一个很大的卖点。 Chrome 操作系统基于 Google 的 Chrome 浏览器，这意味着您可以运行的大多数程序都是基于网络的。没有像 Windows 笔记本电脑上常见的那样需要卸载臃肿软件或不需要的应用程序，它可以在几秒钟内启动，并且您几乎可以同样快地完全重置为出厂设置。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>当然，对于某些用户来说，简单性也是一个主要缺点。如果您是视频编辑器或软件开发人员，则无法安装本机软件可能会成为问题。但也有很多人在浏览器中完成大部分工作。但谷歌及其软件合作伙伴在支持更高级功能方面每年都在进步。例如，Google 在 Chromebook 上的 Google Photos 应用程序中<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://support.google.com/photos/thread/208682996/bring-your-creativity-to-life-with-photos%E2%80%99-new-video-editing-features-on-chromebook?hl=en">添加了视频编辑工具</a>- 它不会取代 Adob​​e Premiere，但对很多人来说应该很方便。</p><p>谷歌还增加了对 Chromebook 上 Android 应用程序的支持，这极大地扩展了可用软件的数量。质量差异很大，但这意味着您可以使用 Chromebook 做更多事情，而不仅仅是基于网络的应用程序。例如，您可以安装 Netflix 应用程序并保存视频以供离线观看。 Microsoft Office 和 Adob​​e Lightroom 等其他 Android 应用程序的功能也令人惊讶。在 Android 应用程序和网络应用程序的全面改进之间，Chromebook 不仅仅是一个浏览器。</p><h2> Chromebook 的优点是什么？ </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-08/38bdd2f0-2488-11ed-affd-31657bb03b0c" alt="三台 Chromebook 笔记本电脑叠放在一起，稍微呈扇形展开，放在木桌上的桌面保护罩上。" data-uuid="24972f7b-1262-3d93-8e2b-f189a92fda1b"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">内森·英格拉汉姆 / Engadget</div></figure><p>简而言之，网络浏览和任何基于网络的内容。浏览、流媒体音乐和视频以及使用各种社交媒体网站是人们在 Chromebook 上最常见的日常任务。正如您所料，它们还可以与照片、文档、Gmail、云端硬盘、Keep 等 Google 服务配合良好。是的，任何可以运行 Chrome 的计算机都可以做到这一点，但 Google Chrome 操作系统的轻量级特性使其成为一个响应灵敏且稳定的平台。</p><p>正如我之前提到的，Chrome 操作系统可以运行 Android 应用程序，因此如果您是 Android 用户，您会发现平台之间存在一些良好的联系。您可以在 Chromebook 上获取手机上的大多数相同应用程序，并保持它们之间的信息同步。您还可以使用某些 Android 手机作为 Chromebook 的安全密钥，或立即限制您的笔记本电脑使用移动数据。</p><p>谷歌继续将安全性视为 Chromebook 的主要差异化因素，我认为这绝对是一个值得考虑的因素。第一道防线是自动更新。 Chrome 操作系统更新可在后台快速下载，只需快速重启即可安装最新版本。谷歌表示，Chromebook 上的每个网页和应用程序也都在自己的沙箱中运行，因此任何安全威胁都包含在各个应用程序中。最后，Chrome 操作系统有一个名为“验证启动”的自检功能，每次设备启动时都会运行。除此之外，您通常无法在 Chromebook 上安装传统应用程序这一简单事实意味着不良行为者访问系统的方式要少得多。</p><p>至于何时避免它们，答案很简单：如果您严重依赖 Windows 或 Mac 的特定本机应用程序，那么您很可能在 Chromebook 上找不到完全相同的选项。在照片和视频编辑等领域尤其如此，但在法律或金融领域也可能如此。许多企业都在使用 Google 的 G 套件软件，但更多企业仍然有 Chromebook 可能无法满足的特定要求。如果您是 iPhone 用户，您还会错过 iPhone 与 iPad 或 Mac 轻松集成的方式。对我来说，最大的缺点是无法在 Chromebook 上访问 iMessage。</p><p>最后，Chromebook 并不是理想的游戏机，尽管随着云游戏的兴起，它们正在成为<em>稍微</em>更合理的选择。 2022 年底，谷歌和一些硬件合作伙伴宣布推动生产带有<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-cloud-gaming-chromebooks-asus-lenovo-acer-130030080.html">云游戏</a>功能的 Chromebook。从硬件角度来看，这意味着笔记本电脑具有更大的屏幕和更高的刷新率，并优化这些笔记本电脑以与 NVIDIA GeForce Now、Xbox Game Pass 和 Amazon Luna 等服务配合使用。显然，您需要互联网连接才能使用这些服务，但好消息是在 Chromebook 上玩现代游戏并非不可能。您可以从 Google Play 商店安装 Android 游戏，但这并不是大多数人想在笔记本电脑上玩游戏时想到的。</p><p>还有另一个潜在的变化即将出现，Valve 和 Google 正在努力将庞大的 Steam 目录引入 Chromebook。目前，Steam 仅在少数更高规格的设备上作为早期 alpha 版本提供，但它的运行效果比我预期的要好得多。 Of course, you&#39;re still not going to run the most demanding games on basic laptops, but the Steam catalog is so vast that there are plenty of titles that worked on the Chromebook I tested it with. Hopefully, Steam will be supported on more devices soon, <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.chromium.org/chromium-os/steam-on-chromeos/">but the list</a> is somewhat limited at the moment.</p><h2> What are the most important specs for a Chromebook? </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-06/28c4bed0-cd37-11eb-a7ff-de290c52cdf7" alt="Acer Chromebook Spin 713" data-uuid="fc221c8a-c134-348a-a3e8-03c468c702c4"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Nathan Ingraham / Engadget</div></figure><p> Chrome OS is lightweight and usually runs well on fairly modest hardware, so the most important thing to look for might not be processor power or storage space. That said, I&#39;d still recommend you get a Chromebook with a relatively recent Intel processor, ideally a 10th-gen or newer Intel i3. Most non-Intel Chromebooks I&#39;ve tried haven&#39;t had terribly strong performance, but that&#39;s starting to change – as we evaluate more of these Chromebooks, we&#39;ll recommend ones that have enough power to be good everyday computers.</p><p> As for RAM, 8GB should be the target, unless you&#39;re looking for a budget model and know that your needs are fairly modest. Storage space is another place where you don&#39;t need to spend too much; 64GB should be fine for almost anyone. If you plan on storing a lot of files locally or loading up your Chromebook with Linux or Android apps, get 128GB. But for what it&#39;s worth, I&#39;ve never felt like I might run out of storage when using Chrome OS.</p><p> Things like the keyboard and display quality are arguably more important than sheer specs. The good news is that you can find less expensive Chromebooks that still have pretty good screens and keyboards that you won&#39;t mind typing on all day. Many cheap Chromebooks still come with tiny, low-resolution displays, but at this point there&#39;s no reason to settle for anything less than 1080p. (If you&#39;re looking for an extremely portable, 11-inch Chromebook, though, you&#39;ll probably end up with a lesser screen.) Obviously, keyboard quality is a bit more subjective, but there are plenty of affordable options that offer strong typing experiences.</p><p> Google has an Auto Update policy for Chromebooks, and while that&#39;s not a spec, per se, it&#39;s worth checking before you buy. Basically, Chromebooks get regular software updates automatically for about six years from their release date (though that can vary from device to device). <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://support.google.com/chrome/a/answer/6220366?hl=en">This support page</a> lists the Auto Update expiration date for virtually every Chromebook ever, but a good rule of thumb is to buy the newest machine you can to maximize your support.</p><h2> How much should I spend?</h2><p> Chromebooks started out notoriously cheap, with list prices often coming in under $300. But as they&#39;ve gone more mainstream, they&#39;ve transitioned from being essentially modern netbooks to the kind of laptop you&#39;ll want to use all day. As such, prices have increased a bit over the last few years. At this point, you should expect to spend at least $400 if you want a solid daily driver. There are still many budget options out there that may be suitable as secondary devices, but Chromebooks that can be an all-day, every-day laptop will cost a bit more.</p><p> There are also plenty of premium Chromebooks that approach or even exceed $1,000, but I don&#39;t recommend spending that much. Generally, that&#39;ll get you a better design with more premium materials, as well as more powerful internals and extra storage space. Of course, you also sometimes pay for the brand name. But, the specs I outlined earlier are usually enough. That said, if money is no object, there are a few really fabulous options out there.</p><p> <strong>See Also:</strong></p><ul><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-laptops-120008636.html"><strong>Best Laptops for 2023</strong></a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-laptops-172033838.html"><strong>Best Gaming Laptops</strong></a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-2-in-1-laptops-173038508.html"><strong>Best 2-in-1 Laptops for 2023</strong></a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-affordable-windows-laptops-123000512.html"><strong>Best Cheap Windows Laptops</strong></a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-laptops-for-students-130054631.html"><strong>Best Laptops for College Students</strong></a></p></li></ul><h2> Best bang for your buck: Lenovo IdeaPad Flex 5i</h2><p><core-commerce id="c041afb984ff410098fa7151948cc5b7" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Lenovo has been making some of the best affordable Chromebooks you can buy for several years now, and the <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWR6WZjttzosh6Ce0d6Fpj3kauddLu2r8ficQD_ifAjY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLenovo-2-1-Chromebook-Computer%2Fdp%2FB09RNCN3YV%3Fth%3D1">IdeaPad Flex 5i</a> is an affordable laptop that provides just about everything you could want in a basic Chromebook. The 13.3-inch, 1080p touchscreen is extremely bright and fairly sharp; I wish it had a taller aspect ratio than 16:9, but it&#39;s pretty common in Chromebooks. This Lenovo Chromebook runs on a 11th-generation Intel Core i3 processor and includes 8GB of RAM and 128GB of storage. While the processor is starting to show its age, it should still be sufficient for most tasks. Eight hours of battery life is pretty good for a laptop in this price range, and the backlit keyboard is excellent for such an affordable device. The key caps feel a little small under my fingers, but that&#39;s the only real complaint I have.</p><p> Other things in the Flex 5i&#39;s favor include that it has both USB-C and USB-A ports, a microSD card slot and a security lock. At three pounds and 0.66 inches thick, it&#39;s not the lightest or slimmest option out there, but it&#39;s totally reasonable considering the price. Finally, the Flex 5i will receive software and security updates until June of 2029, so you can buy this computer and have it covered for years to come.</p><p> Ultimately, the Ideapad Flex 5i hits the sweet spot for a lot of Chromebook buyers out there, providing a level of quality and performance that&#39;s pretty rare to find at this price point. That said, given this laptop has been out for over a year now, we&#39;re keeping an eye out for a replacement from Lenovo, as well as comparable options other manufacturers release.</p><p> The Lenovo Flex 5i is no longer available directly from Lenovo, but you can commonly find it on Amazon for about $400 (as of this writing, it is selling for $368). That&#39;s an outstanding value.</p><h2> Upgrade option: Acer Chromebook Spin 714</h2><p><core-commerce id="95f0b0e58f474f4d9f29d13316b97c4b" data-type="product-list"></p><p></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAX1QeRQ01eSgnQlMtotxLWXdsieMp9lLHwOn72xLOT_S&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAcer-Chromebook-2-Touchscreen-Built%2Fdp%2FB0BJH9LGK8">Acer&#39;s Chromebook Spin 714</a> has long been one of the best premium Chromebook options out there, and this year&#39;s update is no exception. It&#39;s a modest tweak to the 2022 model, but given how good that computer is I have no issues recommending the latest edition. We haven&#39;t tested it yet, but Acer will have a review model for us soon.</p><p> The Spin 714 features a 14-inch, 1900x1200 touchscreen. That works out to a taller 16:10 aspect ratio than you&#39;ll get from the 1080p panels on most Chromebooks. I&#39;m a big fan of taller laptop screens, and while this isn&#39;t as luxurious as the few 3:2 ratio Chromebooks on the market, it&#39;s still a comfortable and high quality screen.</p><p> One noteworthy new feature is the 2K webcam included in the Spin 714. In a world where we&#39;re all doing more video calls than we&#39;d like, having a camera that doesn&#39;t reduce you to a blurry spot is definitely appreciated.</p><p> As for the rest of the hardware, the 13th-generation Intel Core i5 processor should be more than enough power for most tasks, and the keyboard and trackpad on the 2022 model are solid, if not the best. The same can be said for battery life: I got about seven hours using the Spin 714 in my normal daily routine. That&#39;s not exceptional, but it&#39;s in line with what I&#39;ve seen on other i5-powered Chromebooks. Rounding out the hardware is 8GB of RAM and a generous 256GB of storage space. The latest Spin 714 model isn&#39;t listed on Google&#39;s support page, but last year&#39;s model is supported until June 2030; the latest model&#39;s window should run through June of 2031.</p><p> Another bonus is that its hardware meets Google&#39;s recommended specs to run Steam, so gamers might want to give it a shot and see what games they can install.</p><p> Just as the name suggests, the Spin 714 has a 360-degree hinge which lets you use the laptop in tablet mode. I&#39;m not a fan of this convertible design – I don&#39;t know who wants to use a 3-plus pound tablet, but Acer did include a built-in stylus for handwriting notes or drawing in apps like the built-in Chrome Canvas.</p><p> The latest Spin 714 costs $700 – not an unreasonable price for a computer with these specs and built quality. For most people, the Lenovo model will be enough. But, if you&#39;re a serious multitasker, want a better display and keyboard, or just want a computer that&#39;ll last as long as possible, the Acer Spin 714 is easy to recommend. We&#39;ll update this guide once we receive our test model from Acer so we can give updated impressions, particularly on battery life.</p><h2> A good large-screen option: Acer Chromebook 516 GE</h2><p><core-commerce id="71a3b213e2744dcbbd780b3abc02d825" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Acer introduced the <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9BY2VyLUNocm9tZWJvb2stNTE2LUdFLWk1LTEyNDBQL2RwL0IwQlZWVEwzODg_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby0zci0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNzFjYTM1NWUtYmUwNi0zYmEyLWE4NGEtM2U1NWExOWRiYzg0In0&amp;signature=AQAAAeMPwDw6u8YHqYCk03cgZETQzsbwwkoyPvHFf1lC0Mi_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAcer-Chromebook-516-GE-i5-1240P%2Fdp%2FB0BVVTL388%3Fth%3D1">Chromebook 516 GE</a> in the fall of 2022 as part of Google&#39;s push to make devices suitable for cloud gaming, but you don&#39;t need to be a gamer <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/acer-chromebook-516-ge-hands-on-preview-170011142.html">to appreciate this laptop</a> . For $650, you&#39;ll get a 16-inch display with a 2,560 x 1,600 resolution and a 120hz refresh rate. NVIDIA&#39;s GeForce now gaming service supports up to 4K visuals at 120hz on its Ultimate tier so you&#39;ll get to see those benefits. This laptop also supports Steam, yet another reason gamers might be interested in trying it. But even non-gamers should enjoy the 516 GE&#39;s crisp and clear screen and refined hardware.</p><p> It also includes Intel&#39;s 12th-gen Core i7 1240P processor, 8GB of RAM and 256 GB of storage. Given the laptop&#39;s size, it&#39;s good that Acer didn&#39;t skimp on ports here: there&#39;s an HDMI port, USB-C, USB-A, ethernet and a headphone jack. The keyboard has gamer-friendly LED lights that you can customize, but more importantly it&#39;s just a solid and comfortable keyboard, whether you&#39;re playing games or just typing up reports. The trackpad is large and responsive, as well.</p><p> The 516 GE only weighs 3.75 pounds too – pretty light for a laptop with a 16-inch screen. Between the powerful hardware, solid design, good trackpad and keyboard and great screen, anyone who wants a bigger Chromebook will likely be happy with this model. As for support, Google says the 516 GE will continue receiving updates until June of 2030.</p><h2> Honorable mention: HP Dragonfly Pro Chromebook</h2><p><core-commerce id="d51234aaaa91453e94b11f10e2170144" data-type="product-list"></p><p> If you just want the nicest Chromebook you can buy, with top-shelf specs and design, the $999 <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:HP Store;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=8a0e8870-4cf8-4bda-935c-af7c00c28e2b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=HP+Store&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATmD35Ks726xdz2LVY7LDZXAS0u_pQiizwieyaJc96qW&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hp.com%2Fus-en%2Fshop%2Fpdp%2Fhp-dragonfly-pro-chromebook-16gb-bk">HP Dragonfly Pro Chromebook</a> might meet your needs. For starters, the screen is an absolute stand out. It&#39;s a 14-inch, 2,560 x 1,600 touchscreen that maxes out at an extremely bright 1,200 nits.</p><p> The keyboard and trackpad, meanwhile, are probably the best I&#39;ve tested lately. The keyboard has an extremely satisfying clickiness when you&#39;re typing. It&#39;s no mechanical keyboard, but it felt reassuringly solid and there was no real adjustment period needed when I started banging away on this laptop. The large trackpad is excellent, with great responsiveness and a solid click. There&#39;s also a fingerprint reader so you can unlock the laptop without a password, another premium feature that I wish I saw in more Chromebooks.</p><p> From a specs perspective, the Dragonfly Pro includes a 12th-gen Core i5 i5-1235U processor – not the absolute latest, but plenty of power nonetheless. That&#39;s matched with 16GB of RAM and 256GB of storage, and I definitely noticed the extra RAM makes a difference in responsiveness across the board.</p><p> Other niceties include an 8-megapixel webcam, a shooter that exceeds what you&#39;ll find on most laptops, whether they&#39;re in this price range or not. HP did this without resorting to a huge bezel, either – the top bezel is thicker than the ones on the side, but not so much that the laptop feels unbalanced. And the Bang &amp; Olufsen quad speaker setup is shockingly good. With volume set to about 33 percent, the laptop was plenty loud to fill my office, and it was also fairly well balanced, with prominent bass, surprising stereo separation and clear highs. These are definitely some of the best laptop speakers I&#39;ve ever heard.</p><p> That said, there is a major caveat here. The HP Dragonfly Pro&#39;s battery life is poor — under 5 hours poor, which is very disappointing for a $999 laptop. It&#39;s bad enough that I went back and forth on recommending this device. People who don&#39;t travel a lot and do most of their work at their desk might not care, but in that case, why bother getting one of the thinnest and lightest Chromebooks out there?</p><p> The other downside is that you don&#39;t get a variety of ports here – just four USB-C, and no headphone jack. That&#39;s not a total dealbreaker, as I don&#39;t often find myself plugging much into my Chromebooks, but again it&#39;s definitely worth knowing.</p><p> This laptop is otherwise a total delight to use, as it is extremely well built, powerful and features a great keyboard and screen. I definitely wouldn&#39;t recommend it to everyone with these battery issues, but if you want one of the nicest Chromebooks you can buy and don&#39;t spend a ton of time away from a charger (and have plenty of disposable income), you&#39;ll probably enjoy the Dragonfly Pro.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-chromebooks-160054646.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-chromebooks-160054646.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 71ca355e-be06-3ba2-a84a-3e55a19dbc84</guid><dc:creator> Nathan Ingraham</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 06 Jul 2023 19:30:11 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688671811</ingested><modified> 2023-07-06T19:30:31+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[chromeos]]></category><category><![CDATA[chromebook]]></category><category><![CDATA[hp]]></category><category><![CDATA[thebuyersguide]]></category><category><![CDATA[google]]></category><category><![CDATA[commerce]]></category><category><![CDATA[samsung]]></category><category><![CDATA[feature]]></category><category><![CDATA[asus]]></category><category><![CDATA[bts2020]]></category><category><![CDATA[lenovo]]></category><category><![CDATA[laptops]]></category><category><![CDATA[gear]]></category><category><![CDATA[ElectronicEquipment,Instruments&Components]]></category><category><![CDATA[ElectronicsAccessories]]></category><category><![CDATA[OfficeElectronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology&Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Small Businesses]]></category><category><![CDATA[Computing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Nathan Ingraham]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-04/ab871810-96d5-11eb-b5fe-41c2db4984ea" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><med